editorial:
**Idea**: a partition (i, j) with i + j = (m+n+1)/2 splits combined elements into a left half of size ⌈(m+n)/2⌉ and right half. Valid iff `aLeft <= bRight` and `bLeft <= aRight`. Binary search on `i` over the **smaller** array.

```javascript
function findMedianSortedArrays(a, b) {
  if (a.length > b.length) [a, b] = [b, a];
  const m = a.length, n = b.length, half = (m + n + 1) >> 1;
  let lo = 0, hi = m;
  while (lo <= hi) {
    const i = (lo + hi) >> 1;
    const j = half - i;
    const aL = i === 0 ? -Infinity : a[i - 1];
    const aR = i === m ? Infinity : a[i];
    const bL = j === 0 ? -Infinity : b[j - 1];
    const bR = j === n ? Infinity : b[j];
    if (aL <= bR && bL <= aR) {
      if ((m + n) % 2 === 1) return Math.max(aL, bL);
      return (Math.max(aL, bL) + Math.min(aR, bR)) / 2;
    } else if (aL > bR) hi = i - 1;
    else lo = i + 1;
  }
  return 0;
}
```

**Recurrence**: T(m) = T(m/2) + Θ(1).

**Master theorem**: a=1, b=2, f(m)=Θ(1) ⇒ Case 2 ⇒ T(m) = Θ(log m). Overall **Θ(log min(m, n))**.

